From 3ec3302f16d4be8bf6996d53cca8ec9895dd9aa8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Allsopp <david.allsopp@metastack.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jan 2025 14:20:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add --with-stublibs configure option

--with-stublibs is intended for use in opam and allows an additional
directory to be added at the top of $(ocamlc -where)/ld.conf.

(cherry picked from commit f36db142872f5ca0338d6a951fb26be36c611637)

diff --git a/Changes b/Changes
index f5e2df974457604f21f5dadc899debc1ab1dbced..347eaa7dacb385aeac16704aea7361db49296f05 100644
--- a/Changes
+++ b/Changes
@@ -51,6 +51,10 @@ OCaml 4.14 maintenance version
   is dash, rather than bash, this now works correctly).
   (David Allsopp and Samuel Hym, review by Antonin Décimo and Gabriel Scherer)
 
+- #14???: New configure option --with-stublibs allows an additional directory
+  to be added to the start of ld.conf.
+  (David Allsopp, review by ???)
+
 ### Bug fixes:
 
 - #12070, #12075, #13209: auto-detect whether `ar` support @FILE arguments at
